    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require accessible, SEN-friendly menus in school canteens",
        "additional_details": "Many pupils with SEN, including autism and sensory processing difficulties, struggle with current school menus. This can cause anxiety and exclusion at lunchtime. SEN-friendly menus would improve accessibility, confidence, and ensure all pupils can make informed, comfortable food choices.",
        "background": "Require all primary and secondary schools to provide SEN-friendly menus. Current menus can be overwhelming, with complex language and unfamiliar choices. Menus should use simple language, visuals, clear allergens, and consistent layouts to reduce stress and support independence.",
